{"nodes":[
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_hermes_agent","label":"Hermes Agent","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Fastest-growing open-source agent of 2026; ~30% of switchers from Open Claude cite its memory defaults. Proved demand for memory but not that its separate runtime is required."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_three_question_framework","label":"Three-Question Memory Framework (Storage/Injection/Recall)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Every memory system is evaluated by three questions: how things get stored, what is injected at session start, and how old information is recalled."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_storage","label":"Storage (memory)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_injection","label":"Injection (memory)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_recall","label":"Recall (memory)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_frozen_snapshot","label":"Frozen Snapshot","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"A size-capped memory.md (max 2,500 chars) loaded silently every session alongside soul/profile/today's memories; capped on purpose to prevent context blowout since curated facts shouldn't be recalled from long-term every session."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_agent_curated_writes","label":"Agent-Curated Writes (post-turn hook)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"The agent, not the user, decides what to persist based on recency and context; a hook after every turn promotes durable facts (decisions, price changes, preferences) into memory.md, deduping and replacing the most-recent/relevant."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_meta_memory_write_skill","label":"Meta Memory Write Skill","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"A readable/editable skill that holds the rules for what gets saved, so the persistence rules are the user's own and the agent just follows them."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_capture_everything","label":"Capture Everything (full transcripts)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Every turn yields a summary plus a complete transcript filed long-term regardless of importance, enabling perfect recall of any prior conversation and exact citation."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_semantic_recall","label":"Semantic Recall (PGlite + pgvector)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Embeds everything as vectors in a local PGlite/pgvector setup, searches by meaning and keyword, re-ranks for relevance, and context-expands into neighboring conversation. Keyword-only search can't find a 'Stripe' chat when you ask about 'payment processing'."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_cite_sources","label":"Cite Sources on Recall","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"On recall it cites the exact words, who decided, and the date, or says it doesn't know rather than fabricating. Inspired by Garry Tan's Gbrain; matters most for team-based memory where the decision is a teammate's."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_historical_import","label":"Historical Import / Bootstrap","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"'npm run memory import sessions' detects sources, uses Claude Haiku to summarize past conversations, embeds them into long-term storage, and keeps full transcripts so day one isn't empty — Hermes can't import prior conversations."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_teamos","label":"TeamOS (scoped team/client memory)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"One shared brain, every memory tagged by owner, every query filtered by who's asking so teammates see only memories for projects they're part of. Built on Garry Tan's Gbrain idea, extended across team members."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_self_rewriting_loop","label":"Self-Rewriting Loop (Hermes risk)","file_type":"rationale","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Hermes overestimates its own results when editing its own skills, overwriting correct information; users bolt on approval gates and rollback to make it safe. A motivation for owning the system as plain files instead."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_fts5_keyword_search","label":"FTS5 Keyword Search (Hermes recall)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Hermes recalls over sessions in SQLite with FTS5 keyword matching only, so it finds a conversation only when the query contains the exact original words — an acknowledged open issue on its own GitHub."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_recall_ladder","label":"Recall Ladder","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"A progressively deeper recall path: re-ranked meaning+keyword matches expanded to full session transcript, returning an accurate scoped summary plus near-miss matches."},
{"id":"yt_9ciowbmokdu_memory_gbrain","label":"Gbrain (Garry Tan / Y Combinator)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-9CiOwbmOKdU-memory.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/9CiOwbmOKdU","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes","contributor":null,"rationale":"Garry Tan's shared-brain concept that inspired both source-citation on recall and the team-scoped memory (TeamOS)."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_graphify","label":"graphify (knowledge-graph skill)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"An open-source skill for Claude Code/Codex/Cursor/Gemini CLI that turns any folder into a connected knowledge map: reads real code structure (calls/imports) with no AI calls, extracts ideas from PDFs/docs, and uses AI vision on images."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_god_nodes","label":"God Nodes","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"The handful of concepts everything else connects through; on nanoGPT the biggest node was the GPT class itself — graphify found the heart of the codebase on its own."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_honesty_tags","label":"Honesty Tags (Extracted/Inferred/Ambiguous)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Every connection is labeled Extracted (found in files), Inferred (worked out), or Ambiguous (unsure) so the map never pretends to know something it doesn't."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_surprising_connections","label":"Surprising Connections","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Links between things you never realized were related, each with a plain-English explanation of why."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_token_efficiency","label":"Token Efficiency (71x fewer tokens)","file_type":"rationale","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"On a 52-file corpus of repos/papers/images, answering through the graph used 71x fewer tokens than reading raw files; the map is saved to disk so it answers weeks later without rereading the pile."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_export_obsidian","label":"graphify export obsidian","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Turns the knowledge graph into a real Obsidian vault — one note per concept with properties, double-bracket wikilinks per connection, honesty tags carried over, plus a canvas file — because both speak the same open format."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_obsidian_skills","label":"Obsidian Skills (Kepano / Steph Ango, 'the hands')","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Five free skills published by the Obsidian CEO that let an agent write nodes in Obsidian's dialect (wikilinks), build bases tables, draw on canvas, drive the app CLI, and clean web pages via defuddle — the 'hands' that act inside the map."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_bases","label":"Bases (live tables)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_canvas","label":"Canvas File (whiteboard graph)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_obsidian_cli","label":"Obsidian Command Line (100+ commands)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Drives the Obsidian app itself; needs version 1.12+ with a settings switch turned off."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_defuddle","label":"Defuddle (web page to clean markdown)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Strips any web page down to clean markdown — the front door for capturing external content into the graph."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_capture_map_loop","label":"Capture-Map-Ask-Write-Back Loop","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Five steps run as one loop: capture (graphify add URL), the map updates itself, ask the graph instead of reading piles, the agent writes learnings back as linked notes, and the next rebuild picks them up — a second brain that maintains itself."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_watch_mode","label":"Watch Mode / Git-Hook Rebuild","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Run in watch mode to rebuild as files change, or install the git hook so every commit redraws the map automatically."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_lucas_rosati_memory","label":"Claude Code Memory Setup (Lucas Rosati)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"A community repo (800+ stars) pairing Obsidian + graphify as persistent memory for Claude Code: sessions end, the atlas survives — amnesia solved."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_second_brain","label":"Self-Maintaining Second Brain","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Not a chatbot with a folder but a second brain that maintains itself — the atlas that solves both the reread-cost and amnesia problems."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_community_detection","label":"Community Detection","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Groups nodes into communities (e.g. 19 communities on nanoGPT), each rendered as a color on the interactive map."},
{"id":"yt_rtutpot4syg_shortest_path_query","label":"Shortest-Path Query","file_type":"concept","source_file":"yt-rtutpoT4SYg.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://youtu.be/rtutpoT4SYg","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":null,"contributor":null,"rationale":"Ask the graph 'show me the shortest path between these two functions' — on nanoGPT, two hops through the model file, every link labeled extracted."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_three_questions","label":"Three Questions (Store / Inject / Recall)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"The only three jobs a memory system has: store (how a fact is saved), inject (what loads unasked at session start), recall (how old info is found). Claude Code out of the box does all three badly. The three layers are independent — a broken one doesn't break the others."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_frozen_snapshot","label":"Inject: The Frozen Snapshot","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Current priorities, open questions and pending decisions should already be in context before you type. Treat the snapshot as frozen for the session — writes take effect next session — so the model's picture of 'what's true now' stays stable."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_sessionstart_hook","label":"SessionStart Hook","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Reads the working-memory file and today's dated log and injects both silently as background context — no greeting, no recap."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_working_memory_file","label":"Working-Memory File (capped)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"A capped file with fixed sections (active threads, notes worth keeping, pending decisions). Keep the cap small on purpose — a file allowed to grow forever becomes a junk drawer, not memory."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_dated_log_file","label":"Dated Daily Log File","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"A separate per-day log so daily detail doesn't threaten the working-memory cap; also the append target for auto-captured turn summaries."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_agent_curated_writes","label":"Store: Agent-Curated Writes Skill","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"A skill triggered by 'remember'/'note that'/'forget about' that reads the entire working-memory file (the dedup step), then adds/replaces/removes, consolidating if the cap would blow. Judgment rules are editable instructions inside the skill, not hardcoded logic."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_capture_everything","label":"Store: Capture Everything","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"The curated file is an edited highlight reel; separately, every turn is filed durable and unedited so months later you can find the exact conversation a decision came from."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_stop_hook","label":"Stop Hook (turn capture)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Extracts the last exchange from the transcript, has a cheap fast model summarize it to third-person bullets, appends to today's log under an 'auto-captured' section, and archives the raw transcript. Run detached, fire-and-forget, so it never blocks session end."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_idempotent_capture","label":"Idempotent Capture (hash the turn)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Hash the source turn and skip if already written, so re-runs of the capture hook never duplicate entries."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_semantic_search","label":"Recall: Search by Meaning","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Asking about 'payment processing' when the chat said 'Stripe' returns nothing under keyword search — the single most common failure mode. Start simple; add complexity only if you hit its limits."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_vector_database","label":"Local Vector Database + Embedding Model","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"A project-local vector DB with a consistent embedding model; re-embed everything if you switch models."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_hybrid_search","label":"Hybrid Search (vector + keyword)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Vector and keyword search run in parallel then merge, so neither exact-word nor meaning-only failures are fatal."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_rerank","label":"Rerank by Recency / Source Weight","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"A cheap rerank by recency and source weight before returning merged results."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_chunking_strategy","label":"Chunking by Natural Breaks","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Split by natural breaks (headings, sessions), not fixed windows, so chunks stay semantically coherent."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_cite_source","label":"Recall: Cite the Source","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Keep source file, date and heading on every chunk and surface them on recall — 'here's what was said, when, and where it lives'. Vague recall is fine for jogging your own memory but a liability for a teammate's or client's decision."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_bootstrap","label":"Bootstrap: Don't Start From Zero","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Walk existing session history at install time, extract meaningful turns the same way the capture hook does, summarize into dated logs, and index them, so day one isn't empty."},
{"id":"claude_code_memory_plan_sentinel_file","label":"Sentinel File (run-once guard)","file_type":"concept","source_file":"claude-code-memory-plan.md","source_location":null,"source_url":"https://scrapeshq.notion.site/i-gave-claude-code-hermes-s-best-feature-steal-this","captured_at":"2026-07-21","author":"Simon Scrapes / Agentic Academy","contributor":null,"rationale":"Guards the one-time historical import so it only ever runs once."}
